The lifetimes \(X_1\) and \(X_2\) are independent and identically distributed exponential random variables with mean \(\theta = 2\). The cost is defined as \(Z = 2Y_1 + Y_2\), where \(Y_1 = \min(X_1, X_2)\) and \(Y_2 = \max(X_1, X_2)\).

The expected value of \(Y_1\), the minimum of two i.i.d. exponential random variables with mean \(\theta = 2\), is \(E(Y_1) = \theta / 2 = 2 / 2 = 1\).

The sum \(Y_1 + Y_2 = X_1 + X_2\), so \(E(Y_1 + Y_2) = E(X_1 + X_2) = E(X_1) + E(X_2) = 2 + 2 = 4\). Therefore, \(E(Y_2) = E(Y_1 + Y_2) - E(Y_1) = 4 - 1 = 3\).

