(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The problem involves finding \(P(Y_7 < 27.3)\), where \(Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8\) are the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \(\pi_{0.7} = 27.3\). This means \(P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7\) for a single observation \(X\).

For a continuous distribution, \(P(Y_7 < 27.3) = P(Y_7 \leq 27.3)\). The event \(Y_7 \leq 27.3\) is equivalent to having at least 7 of the 8 observations less than or equal to 27.3. The number of observations \(S\) less than or equal to 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \(n = 8\) and \(p = 0.7\), so \(S \sim \text{Binomial}(8, 0.7)\).

Thus,  
\[
P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(S \geq 7) = P(S = 7) + P(S = 8).
\]

Calculate each probability:  
\[
P(S = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3)^1 = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]  
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543, \quad \text{so} \quad 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032.
