- Upper bound: \(z_2 = \frac{54.453 - 54.030}{0.84597} \approx 0.500\)

The probability \(P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)\) corresponds to \(P(-1.500 \leq Z \leq 0.500)\) for a standard normal variable \(Z\).  
- \(P(Z \leq 0.500) \approx 0.6915\)  
- \(P(Z \leq -1.500) \approx 0.0668\)  
- \(P(-1.500 \leq Z \leq 0.500) = 0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247\)

The result is rounded to four decimal places as it is a probability and consistent with the precision of the inputs.

