(a) Find the probability that the length of life of the bulb from company $A$ exceeds the length of life of the bulb from company $B$ by at least 15 hours.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The lengths of life for bulbs from company A and company B are normally distributed: \(X \sim N(800, 14400)\) and \(Y \sim N(850, 2500)\). The probability that the life of bulb A exceeds that of bulb B by at least 15 hours is \(P(X > Y + 15)\), or equivalently \(P(X - Y > 15)\).

