Standardize the value 15:  
\[
z = \frac{15 - (-50)}{130} = \frac{65}{130} = 0.5
\]

The probability is \(P(Z > 0.5)\) where \(Z\) is a standard normal variable. Using the standard normal distribution, \(P(Z > 0.5) = 1 - P(Z < 0.5) = 1 - 0.6915 = 0.3085\).

