\[
\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \approx 0.8660254, \quad S = 0.8660254 \times 1.0545718 \times 10^{-34} \approx 9.13286 \times 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s}.
\]

The result is approximately \( 9.13286 \times 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s} \). In the required units of \( 10^{-35} \, \text{J} \cdot \text{s} \), the numerical coefficient is 9.13286. Rounding to three significant figures, as Planck's constant has high precision but the context allows reasonable rounding, gives 9.13.

